        <h1>Documentation: Simple App Using Clerk</h1>
        <p>This authentication app is built using Clerk with Next.js, streamlining authentication without manual session handling and password management.</p>
        
        <h2>Why Clerk?</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Secure and scalable authentication with minimal setup.</li>
            <li>Built-in multi-factor authentication, social logins, and email/password authentication.</li>
            <li>Optimized for Next.js with API route integration.</li>
            <li>JWT-based authentication for secure API interactions.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <h3>Backend:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Next.js (API Routes), Clerk SDK</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Frontend:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Next.js, Clerk React SDK</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Setup & Run</h2>
        <h3>1. Prerequisites</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Node.js (v16+), Clerk Account</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>2. Clone & Install</h3>
        <pre><code>git clone &lt;repository-url&gt;
cd clerk-nextjs-app
npm install</code></pre>
        
        <h3>3. Configure Clerk</h3>
        <p>Set up Clerk API keys in your <code>.env.local</code> file:</p>
        <pre><code>CLERK_FRONTEND_API=your-clerk-frontend-api
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=your-clerk-secret-key
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-clerk-publishable-key</code></pre>
        
        <h3>4. Run the App</h3>
        <p>Development Mode:</p>
        <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
        <p>Production Mode:</p>
        <pre><code>npm run build
npm start</code></pre>
        <p>Access at: <code>http://localhost:3000</code>.</p>
        
